Nostalgia has a name, and it's grilled cheese! Relive the glory of the melty,
toasty classic with this grown-up take on everyone's favorite sandwich. The
addition of umami-packed sun-dried tomato aioli brings surprising new depth to
the elevated combo of mozzarella and cheddar between slices of buttery toasted
sourdough. Cap off your meal with a side salad of peppery arugula dressed in
tangy-sweet balsamic vinaigrette.

== Sun-Dried Tomato Aioli ==

Wash and dry produce.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @Sun-Dried Tomato Paste{1%ounce},
@Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, and @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon} until combined. (Be
sure to measure the garlic powder—we sent more!)

> For 4 servings, use ¼ tsp garlic powder.

== Bacon ==

Heat a #large dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Bacon{4%ounce}; cook,
turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy,
~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Wipe
out pan.

== Grilled Cheese ==

Lay @Sourdough Bread{4%slice} out on a clean work surface.

Spread one side of each bread slice with aioli.

Evenly layer half the bread slices with @Mozzarella Cheese{½%cup} and
@White Cheddar Cheese{½%cup}; top with remaining bread slices, aioli sides
down, to form sandwiches.

Add bacon to bread slices along with mozzarella and cheddar.

Heat @Butter{3%tablespoon}(divided) and a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in
a #large pan{} over medium heat.

Add sandwiches and cook, gently pressing with a #spatula{}, until bread is
golden and cheese melts, ~{2-4%minutes} per side, adding an additional 1 TBSP
butter when flipping.

> Work in batches if necessary, adding more butter if needed; lower heat if
> browning too quickly.

Use pan used for bacon here.

== Balsamic Arugula Salad ==

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @Balsamic Glaze{5%teaspoon} and
@Olive Oil{2%teaspoon}; season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. (Be sure to measure
the balsamic glaze—we sent more!)

Add @Arugula{2%ounce} to bowl with vinaigrette; toss to coat. Taste and season
with salt and pepper if desired.

== To Serve ==

Halve sun-dried tomato grilled cheese sandos on a diagonal; divide between
plates. Serve with salad on the side.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.